<p>The fixed nodes are installed on the ceiling of the dining room to reduce isolation. The bi-directional ranging method is used to convert the distance 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm55">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>l</mi>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>l</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>l</mi>
      <mn>3</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> between the fixed nodes and the mobile node into a two-dimensional distance 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm56">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mn>3</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. Then, the trilateral positioning algorithm is used to calculate the robot location coordinates [
 <xref rid="B9-sensors-19-04980" ref-type="bibr">9</xref>].
</p>
